modules.description: Provides functions for defining and validating GraphQL schemas using OCaml's type system. Works with custom type definitions that map to GraphQL object types, interfaces, and unions. Used to enforce strict type checking between client queries and server responses.

Parses GraphQL queries and schemas from strings into structured document representations. Works with complex types like operations, fragments, fields, and directives. Used to analyze and transform GraphQL syntax for validation or code generation.
